# Sane Router

## Goal

Route work to the correct Sane-managed surface or concrete pack skill.

## Use When

- installing, updating, or removing Sane-managed skills, overlays, hooks, or custom agents
- previewing or applying Sane config-backed routing defaults
- deciding which concrete Sane-managed skill or agent should own a task

## Don't Use When

- normal coding, review, or research work already covered by a concrete repo or pack skill
- general repo work with no Sane-managed install/export/config impact

## Inputs

- current task
- current Sane config
- installed pack state and managed asset state

## Outputs

- one concrete next action:
  - preview
  - apply
  - remove
  - inspect
  - route to a specific skill or agent

